## Step 3: Copy the files

From the `claude-overnight` repo, copy these files into your project:

```bash
# Required
cp scripts/review.sh        <your-project>/scripts/review.sh
cp .claude/commands/build.md <your-project>/.claude/commands/build.md

# Make executable
chmod +x <your-project>/scripts/review.sh

# Create directories
mkdir -p <your-project>/reviews
mkdir -p <your-project>/.claude/local
touch <your-project>/reviews/.gitkeep

# Gitignore ephemeral state
echo '.claude/local/' >> <your-project>/.gitignore
```

### What each file does

| File | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `scripts/review.sh` | Calls Codex/Gemini headless, parses fenced JSON verdicts, returns exit codes. Supports single + parallel multi-reviewer. |
| `.claude/commands/build.md` | The `/build` command — deterministic state machine that orchestrates plan → review → implement → review. |
| `reviews/` | Durable review artifacts (committed to git). |
| `.claude/local/` | Ephemeral per-branch state files (gitignored). |

