## Step 4: Add the rules (optional but recommended)

Add this to your project's `.claude/rules/` or `CLAUDE.md`:

```markdown
## Cross-Model Review (Default Behavior)

All planning uses Codex review by default. The `/build` command has four explicit modes:

| Mode | Flag | NL triggers | What happens |
|------|------|-------------|--------------|
| `just_plan` | `--mode just_plan` | "just plan", "skip review" | Claude plans, no external review |
| `plan_review` | `--mode plan_review` | "plan this out" (DEFAULT) | Claude plans → Codex reviews |
| `full_review` | `--mode full_review` | "full review", "with gemini" | Claude plans → Codex + Gemini review in parallel |
| `research_review` | `--mode research_review` | "current research", "latest info" | Research agents → Claude plans → Codex reviews |

Gemini is opt-in only — never used unless explicitly requested.
Ambiguity defaults to plan_review. Overnight sessions MUST use explicit --mode flags.
```

