## Usage

```bash
# Default — Codex reviews plan and implementation
/build "add user authentication"

# Explicit mode
/build --mode plan_review "add user authentication"

# Full review — Codex + Gemini in parallel
/build --mode full_review "add user authentication"

# Research first — gather current-month info before planning
/build --mode research_review "evaluate auth libraries"

# Just plan, no review
/build --mode just_plan "add user authentication"

# Override reviewer
/build --reviewer gemini "add user authentication"
/build --reviewer codex,gemini "add user authentication"
```

Natural language also works:
- "plan this out" → `plan_review`
- "full review" or "with gemini" → `full_review`
- "current research" or "latest info" → `research_review`
- "just plan" → `just_plan`

